  "texts": [
    "All data are given as means and standard error of the mean.",
    "A p-value < 0.05 was considered statistically significant.",
    "ResultsA total of 150 wrist radiographs from the Division of Hand, Plastic and Aesthetic Surgery within the LMU University Hospital Munich were included in this study.",
    "Among the 100 distal radius fractures, 20 fractures were classified as type A, 4 as type B, and 76 as type C according to the AO classification for distal radius fracture.We conducted an analysis of the sensitivity (n = 100) and specificity (n = 50) of ChatGPT 4, hand surgery resident, medical student and Gleamer BoneView™ for distal radius fracture detection.",
    "McNemar's test was conducted for statistical comparison (Fig. 3)."
